                                    p Samarkand! One of the oldest cities in the world, the cradle of world civilization, the capital of ancient Sogdiana and the empire of Amir Temur, the same age as Rome, Thebes and Athens. "Eden of the Ancient East", "Face of the Earth", "Pearl of the Muslim World" - this is how ancient and modern authors call Samarkand.
                                    p Samarkand, city in east-central Uzbekistan that is one of the oldest cities of Central Asia and the second largest city in Uzbekistan after Tashkent . For thousands of years Samarkand prospered being located on one of the major trade routes to China. This famous city has got so many nick-names that they can really describe people's attitude to it: the Mirror of the World, the Jewel of Islam, the Garden of Soul, the Center of the Universe.
