                                .room-exerpt
                                    .room-price.mb-4
                                    p In Sanskrit word Bukhara signifies "monastery" and this city was once a large commercial center on the Great Silk Road. Bukhara was first mentioned in Chinese chronicles in the early 5th century BC. It is one of the oldest trade and cultural centers in Central Asia.
                                    p The city itself was founded by Persian Prince who built a citadel there after he had married to Afrosiab's daughter in Samarkand. But the growth of the city mostly depended on its strategic location.
